<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1159,1400]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Geographical distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[510,622,1196,1220]" name="Honduras" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[639,752,1196,1220]" name="Colombia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[768,886,1196,1220]" name="Venezuela" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[902,1130,1196,1220]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Trinidad &amp; Tobago</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1238,1196,1219]" name="Panama" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1255,1345,1196,1220]" name="Guyana" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1432,1196,1220]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,205,1232,1255]" name="Peru" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[216,301,1231,1255]" name="Bolivia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[360,466,1232,1256]" name="Paraguay" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus and Polhemus" box="[629,988,1231,1255]" firstAuthor="Polhemus" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="204 - 216" refId="ref42180" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (1991) A review of the veliid fauna of bromeliads, with a key and description of a new species (Heteroptera: Veliidae). Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 99, 204 - 216." type="journal article" year="1991">Polhemus and Polhemus (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, the record from 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1252,1231,1255]" name="Belize" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belize</collectingCountry>
(cited as 
<collectingCountry name="Belize" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">British Honduras</collectingCountry>
) present on 
<bibRefCitation author="Drake and Maldonado-Capriles" box="[406,847,1268,1292]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="47 - 54" refId="ref37258" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Maldonado-Capriles, J. (1952) Water striders from Territorio Amazonas of Venezuela (Hemiptera: Hydrometridae, Veliidae). Great Basin Naturalist, 12, 47 - 54." type="journal article" year="1952">Drake and Maldonado-Capriles (1952)</bibRefCitation>
is probably an error, because only specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,260,1303,1327]" name="Honduras" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Honduras</collectingCountry>
proper were found in Drake’s collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
